<TITLE> Hajj flights to start from Oct 21 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 30 (bdnews24.com)  The authorities have decided to start the Hajj flight from Oct 21 and the return flights will take place from Dec 1. State minister for religion affairs Md Shahjahan said this to reporters on Wednesday after an inter-ministerial meeting on the transportation of Hajjis and Hajj management at his office. This yearsome eight thousand and 35 people will go to Hajj under government management and 50 thousand and 420 people will go under private arrangements. Already, accommodation of seven thousand and 753 Hajjis under government management has been ensured in rented houses. Accommodation of the rest will be arranged within next week, he said. Two hundred and 50 Hajj agencies have been approved this year to handle the Hajjis under private management. Among them, 233 agencies have rented houses and received visas. The work of getting visa by the rest 17 agencies will be completed within next week, he said. This year Saudi airlines will carry 20 thousand and Bangladesh Biman will carry 38 thousand 663 Hajjis. For this, Biman has taken initiatives to charter two aircraft. Already, one aircraft has been chartered. The process of hiring another will be completed in two weeks, said the minister. He expressed hope that no anomalies would take place this year like it happened in the previous years. Ministry officials, Hajj management officials and representatives of Hajj agencies were present at the meeting. bdne
